# Session 11 - [2/26] 

CSS Layout Evolution
tables (90s) to floats (2000s) to flexbox (2010s = one dimensional layouts)
to grid (2017+ = 2d layouts)
--- today we use flexbox and grid together

flexbox basics:
.container {
  display: flex;
}

- makes all direct children flex items whihc:
line up in a row (thru default)
shrink/grow to fit
easily alignable

WHEN TO USE FLEXBOX - 
Content flows in one direction; Items to determine their own size; Alignment within a row/column

WHEN TO USE GRID - 
Need rows AND columns; Need precise control over layout; Complex page structures
